<TEXT>
a united airlines flight with 83 people 
on board made an emergency landing sunday after the plane lost 
cabin pressure en route from chicago to spokane wash officials 
said 
there were no serious injuries but 16 people were taken to two 
hospitals for treatment of earaches and nausea all were treated 
and released 
the traffic control tower at billings logan international 
airport said it received the pilots call for medical help just 
before 230 pm and sent out a request for all available 
assistance 
a dozen fire trucks and ambulances were on hand when the boeing 
737300 made a safe landing and taxied to a stop just east of the 
terminal 
united flight 793 had 78 passengers three flight attendants a 
pilot and copilot said ray anderson the airlines billings 
manager 
the plane was at an altitude of about 37000 feet and flying 
over miles city 146 miles east of billings when lost some if its 
pressure said tom binford assistant director of aviation here 
anderson said pressure stabilized on the plane when it reached 
an altitude of 19000 feet 
it already had been a bumpy flight from chicago said passenger 
mary burnham of newtown conn who was flying with her husband and 
two children to visit friends in missoula 
everybody knew something was wrong burnham said after the 
landing you could feel it in your ears they wanted to land in 
miles city but there wasnt enough runway 
