<TEXT>
about 1000 soviet children with health 
problems caused by the 1986 chernobyl nuclear plant explosion are 
in cuba for medical treatment at a specially designed center the 
countrys news agency says 
the group of 300 children that arrived sunday was the fourth to 
come to havana this month for treatment of illnesses related to the 
ukrainian power plant disaster prensa latina said in a dispatch 
the agency said cuban president fidel castro had welcomed a 
group of 255 who arrived on july 2 it said about 1000 children 
from the chernobyl area are being treated in a specially designed 
medical center 
we have all the conditions to do it and we are doing it very 
gladly castro told reporters according to the news agency 
the medical center called pioneer city is located east of 
havana on the oceanfront the complex includes 520 houses two 
hospitals 15 dining halls amusement parks video and movie 
houses the agency said 
at least 31 deaths are officially blamed on the april 26 1986 
explosion and fire at the chernobyl nuclear plant the actual toll 
is much higher and includes people stricken with radiationrelated 
diseases 
