<TEXT>
teams of college engineers begin a race with the 
sun monday 
thirtytwo college and university teams take off from orlando 
fla for an 11day jaunt in solar powered cars hoping to prove 
the efficiency of their designs as the auto industry looks for ways 
other than gasoline to power vehicles 
the route covers more than 1600 miles of secondary state and 
county roads in eight states and the contestants are bound to 
attract some curious stares along the way 
the vehicles are a long way from any assembly line one of the 
chief considerations goes to wind resistance which means that the 
cars hug the ground are basically flat and have no styling 
excesses 
it wont necessarily be the fastest car that wins said 
general motors corp vice president donald l runkle instead it 
will be the car performing most efficiently 
