qualifying heats to determine the order of start on monday 
we want to make sure they are all roadworthy gm spokesman 
dave sloan said friday 
cars are entered from a variety of colleges and universities 
ranging from tiny crowder college in neosho mo to the university 
of texas and massachusetts institute of technology teams from 
puerto rico and canada also are entered 
each team received 5000 from gm and 2000 from the energy 
department along with whatever funds could be raised through the 
school local and state governments or elsewhere 
thats only part of the investment for instance about 750000 
has been spent on the car from the university of michigan 
vehicles will start each day at 30 second intervals with the 
previous days winner going first average speeds are expected to 
be in the 30 mph range crews will be allowed to charge batteries 
for two hours before and after each days racing 
the winner will be the team with the least total elapsed time 
the course passes through florida georgia alabama tennessee 
kentucky ohio and indiana before winding up at the gm technical 
center in warren mich north of detroit on the afternoon of july 
19 
the top three finishers will be sponsored by gm in worldwide 
solar car competition later this year in australia gms sunraycer 
solar vehicle won the first worldwide solar car race in 1987 
the sunraycer is on display in the smithsonian institution 
